  Dialogue:
  - What existed in <color=cyan>Belo Monte</color>? The <color=00FFBF>bard</color>
    asked this question several times in his song, but never answered it. This made
    <color=purple>William</color> curious.
  - Hey <color=#00FFBF>bard</color>, I'll buy you a drink if you answer a question.
  - I will be happy to answer you, <color=purple>young man</color>.
  - What was in <color=cyan>Belo Monte</color>?
  - The <color=#00FFBF>bard</color> laughed.
  - This is a very difficult question, my friend. What would motivate a man to fight
    an invincible enemy?
  - There are no invincible enemies.
  - You're absolutely right, there's a legendary battle where peasants defeated an
    entire army, even though they were incredibly outnumbered. The only strength
    they had was a deep desire to protect their families and their land.
  - You bards exaggerate everything, that's impossible.
  - The <color=#00FFBF>bard</color> smiled.
  - You're absolutely right!
  - Whatever, I liked this song, I'm going to learn to play it.
  - The <color=#00FFBF>bard</color> laughed.
  - A warrior learning to play a song where the national army is the villain. This
    is the first time I've seen it.
  - The army is the villain? I didn't even notice.
  - Great! We bards write our songs subtly so the warriors don't realize we're doing
    propaganda against them.
  - Aren't you afraid to say that in front of a warrior?
  - The <color=#00FFBF>bard</color> smiled kindly.
  - No.
  - Whatever, your music put me in a good mood. If you teach me how to play it, I'll
    pretend I didn't hear that.
  - It will be my pleasure to teach you, <color=purple>young man</color>.
  DialogueBR:
  - "O que existia em <color=cyan>Belo Monte</color>? O <color=00FFBF>bardo</color>
    fez essa pergunta v\xE1rias vezes em sua m\xFAsica, mas nunca respondeu. Isso
    deixou <color=purple>William</color> curioso."
  - "Ei <color=#00FFBF>bardo</color>, eu te pago uma bebida se voc\xEA responder
    a uma pergunta."
  - Ficarei feliz em te responder, <color=purple>jovem</color>.
  - O que existia em <color=cyan>Belo Monte</color>?
  - O <color=#00FFBF>bardo</color> riu.
  - "Esta \xE9 uma pergunta muito dif\xEDcil, meu amigo. O que motivaria um homem
    a lutar contra um inimigo invenc\xEDvel?"
  - "N\xE3o existem inimigos invenc\xEDveis."
  - "Voc\xEA est\xE1 absolutamente certo, teve uma batalha lend\xE1ria em que camponeses
    derrotaram um ex\xE9rcito inteiro, mesmo estando em n\xFAmero bem menor. A \xFAnica
    for\xE7a que tinham era um profundo desejo de proteger suas fam\xEDlias e suas
    terras."
  - "Voc\xEAs bardos exageram em tudo, isso \xE9 imposs\xEDvel."
  - O <color=#00FFBF>bardo</color> sorriu.
  - "Voc\xEA est\xE1 absolutamente certo!"
  - "Tanto faz, eu gostei dessa m\xFAsica, vou aprender a toc\xE1-la"
  - O <color=#00FFBF>bardo</color> riu.
  - "Um guerreiro aprendendo a tocar uma m\xFAsica onde o ex\xE9rcito nacional \xE9
    o vil\xE3o. \xC9 a primeira vez que vejo isso."
  - "O ex\xE9rcito \xE9 o vil\xE3o? nem percebi.."
  - "Excelente! N\xF3s bardos escrevemos nossas can\xE7\xF5es sutilmente para que
    os guerreiros n\xE3o percebam que estamos fazendo propaganda contra eles."
  - "Voc\xEA n\xE3o tem medo de dizer isso na frente de um guerreiro?"
  - O <color=#00FFBF>bardo</color> sorriu gentilmente.
  - "N\xE3o."
  - "Seja como for, sua m\xFAsica me deixou de bom humor. Se voc\xEA me ensinar a
    tocar, vou fingir que n\xE3o ouvi isso."
  - "Ser\xE1 um prazer ensin\xE1-lo, <color=purple>jovem</color>."
